{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17409521","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17409521"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T04:50:33+09:30","options":[0],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T04:50:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260850"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260850"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12531"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17475122","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17475122"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:29:15+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:29:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12531"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260850","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1260850"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T04:50:21+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T04:55:49+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"new","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":1,"questionsAnswered":1,"marksTotal":1,"marksAttainable":1,"marksAttempted":1,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T04:50:33+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":1,"questionsCorrect":1,"marksCorrect":1},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"12531","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12531"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.78,0.06,0.05,0.04,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5030"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"46194"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5030","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5030"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12531"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"31119"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1853"},{"type":"tags","id":"6222"},{"type":"tags","id":"11198"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8352"},{"type":"contributions","id":"9853"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"46194","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/46194"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA three-year-old boy presents to the General Practice clinic with his mother who is concerned that he has not been able to run with other children in the playground. She says he has been slow and clumsy, and has also been having difficulty climbing stairs and jumping. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. He has hypertrophied calf muscles and hypotonia in the distal lower limbs. The general practitioner orders a creatine kinase (CK) level which is 2,500 U/L (30-200).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following eponymous signs would you expect to be positive in this patient?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Gower\u0027s sign","Las\u00e8gue sign","Brudzi\u0144ski sign","Prehn\u0027s sign","Romberg\u0027s sign"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis is a child presenting with Duchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD). Duchenne and Becker muscular dystrophy (BMD) are X-linked recessive disorders caused by mutations in the DMD gene which encodes dystrophin, a protein which binds to the sarcolemma and protects from enzymatic degradation. The breakdown of muscle fibers preferentially affects lower limbs and proximal muscles, which leads to muscle weakness and the clinical features described in this case, including difficulty walking, running, and jumping with pseudohypertrophy and lower motor neuron dysfunction on examination. Some children with dystrophinopathies may use their hand to support themselves while standing up from the floor. This is known as \u003Cstrong\u003EGower\u0027s sign\u003C/strong\u003E and should prompt investigation in any child who presents with these symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDMD exists at the severe end of the muscular dystrophy spectrum and typically presents earlier (mean age of diagnosis is 3-4 years) with more severe symptoms, thus matching the child in this case. BMD is more likely to present later (5-60 years of age) with a milder phenotype. An elevated CK is compatible with the diagnosis of muscular dystrophy but definitive diagnosis is achieved using genetic testing or muscle biopsy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELas\u00e8gue sign\u003C/strong\u003E is pain caused by 30-70 degrees of leg extension in the supine position, and is indicative of lumbar radiculopathy. \u003Cstrong\u003EBrudzi\u0144ski sign\u003C/strong\u003E is involuntary flexion of the hips and knees secondary to neck flexion and is indicative of meningeal irritation. When elevation of the testes causes relief of pain it is known as \u003Cstrong\u003EPrehn\u0027s sign\u003C/strong\u003E and is typically positive in epididymitis, but negative in testicular torsion. \u003Cstrong\u003ERomberg\u0027s sign\u003C/strong\u003E is impaired coordination when asking a patient to stand with their eyes closed, arms raised and feet together. This is indicative of impaired proprioception.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["A child who requires the use of their hands to stand up from the floor is known as Gower\u0027s sign and should raise suspicion for dystrophinopathy."],"references":["Birnkrant DJ, Bushby K, Bann CM, Apkon SD, Blackwell A, Brumbaugh D, Case LE, Clemens PR, Hadjiyannakis S, Pandya S, Street N, Tomezsko J, Wagner KR, Ward LM, Weber DR; DMD Care Considerations Working Group. Diagnosis and management of Duchenne muscular dystrophy, part 1: diagnosis, and neuromuscular, rehabilitation, endocrine, and gastrointestinal and nutritional management. Lancet Neurol. 2018 Mar;17(3):251-267. doi: 10.1016/S1474-4422(18)30024-3. Epub 2018 Feb 3. Erratum in: Lancet Neurol. 2018 Apr 4;: PMID: 29395989; PMCID: PMC5869704."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"31119"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12531"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"31119","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/31119"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-05-30T19:58:00+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-05-30T19:58:27+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5030"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"46194"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"